OL,3,CIsrael and Lebanon leaders to speak as
OL,4,Cmore US troops sent to Middle East
OL,6,FIran's foreign minister, Abbas
OL,7,FAraghchi, took part in a preliminary
OL,8,Fmeeting with Asim Munir, Pakistan's
OL,9,Farmy chief of staff, Iranian state
OL,10,Fmedia reported. It said talks would
OL,11,Fcontinue on Thursday.
OL,13,FMediators are pushing for a compromise
OL,14,Fon three main sticking points that
OL,15,Fderailed direct talks last weekend,
OL,16,FIran's nuclear program, the Strait of
OL,17,FHormuz and compensation for wartime
OL,18,Fdamages, according to a regional
OL,19,Fofficial involved in the mediation
OL,20,Fefforts.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776373859
OL,3,CIsrael and Lebanon leaders to speak as
OL,4,Cmore US troops sent to Middle East
OL,6,FBut even as mediators worked for
OL,7,Fpeace, tensions simmered.
OL,9,FA newly-appointed military adviser to
OL,10,FIranian Supreme Leader Mojtaba
OL,11,FKhamenei said he doesn't support
OL,12,Fextending the ceasefire.
OL,14,FIranian state media quoted Mohsen
OL,15,FRezaei, a former commander in the
OL,16,FIranian Revolutionary Guard, as
OL,17,Fsaying: "Unlike the Americans who are
OL,18,Fafraid of continuous war, we are fully
OL,19,Fprepared and familiar with a long war."
OL,26,@yD@IOU{D@gO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
