OL,3,CIsrael and Lebanon leaders to speak as
OL,4,Cmore US troops sent to Middle East
OL,6,FSince the war began, Iran has
OL,7,Fcurtailed maritime traffic through the
OL,8,FStrait of Hormuz, which a fifth of
OL,9,Fglobal oil transits in peacetime.
OL,10,FTehran's effective closure of the
OL,11,Fstrait sent oil prices skyrocketing,
OL,12,Fraising the cost of fuel, food and
OL,13,Fother basic goods far beyond the
OL,14,FMiddle East.
OL,16,FThe fighting has killed at least 3,000
OL,17,Fpeople in Iran, more than 2,100 in
OL,18,FLebanon, 23 in Israel and more than a
OL,19,Fdozen in Gulf Arab states. Thirteen US
OL,20,Fservice members have also been killed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
